					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13340316#post-4657511</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13340316/scp-5570#post-4657511</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 22 May 2020 06:08:50 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>isaacmayer9</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2807755</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This is a fun story, and I love the idea that the Foundation runs a paranormal investigation agency as a front. Definitely earned a +1 from me. I do question the usage of &quot;pending&quot; — unless these video logs are meant to be occuring in real time as we read, it seems pretty clear what the anomaly is. Maybe add an offset page where the SCP is just the crystal ball, label it &quot;safe,&quot; and include the ending of the story as an addendum. Just a thought — it's still a fun read as is.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
